I. Introduction

Edge Intelligence [1]–[3], evolved from edge computing with the support of artificial intelligence (AI), introduces a paradigm shift for AIoT (AI of Things), which utilizes end devices for making intelligent decisions and responses in real-time. Since AIoT collects raw data closely at the user side, privacy issues have received a great deal of attention globally. For example, the European Commission approved the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) in 2016 to protect personal data and privacy [4].
